reporting-org.narrative: The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria

title.narrative: A multi stakeholder approach to support the implementation of national strategies to reach Malaria elimination in Guatemala by 2022

description.narrative: Guatemala - Malaria - Ministry of Health and Social Assistance of the Republic of Guatemala - MSPAS. This program has the following goals: Break the transmission of autochthonous malaria by Plasmodium vivax by 2020. Continue breaking the transmission by Plasmodium falciparum. The objectives of this program are: Contribute to implementing the planned interventions and activities relating to integrated vector management based on the stratification of malaria transmission risk, which will be supplemented and extended to local areas, as set out in the testing, treatment, research and response operational strategy. Cooperate in the implementation of the strategy and priority interventions and activities to improve and optimize case detection and management, with particular emphasis on the passive and active detection of cases, parasitological diagnosis and suitable treatment under the testing, treatment, research and response operational strategy. Contribute to implementing the surveillance system for malaria elimination at the national, departmental and local levels through staff training, enabling them to undertake active and passive searches for cases and to investigate cases and outbreak locations. Support improved universal access to early diagnosis and timely treatment of malaria, in line with the testing, treatment, research and response operational strategy. the interventions and activities planned as part of the National Strategic Program (NSP) for malaria, program management and the Principal Recipient as defined in this Global Fund grant for malaria; management of the procurement and supply chain and the laboratory systems,. Promote community and social participation through the full involvement of volunteers
